To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Delaware Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Internal evaluation or pilot assessment reports that summarize performance, adoption, risks, or “lessons learned” from the Delaware Mobile ID (IDEMIA) program between January 1, 2023 and the present.

Agreements, contracts, or memoranda of understanding with vendors or partners involved in mDL programs, including but not limited to IDEMIA, AAMVA, Apple, Google, Samsung, or other providers.

Interagency or interstate coordination documents, including but not limited to MOUs or correspondence with AAMVA or other states regarding mDL interoperability, standards development, or airport integration.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 15 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jonathan Rudenberg, a citizen of Delaware, in coordination with Rebecca Williams.

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Colorado Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Evaluation or pilot assessment reports on Colorado’s mDL program since January 1, 2023.

Agreements or contracts with vendors, including but not limited to Apple, Google, AAMVA, IDEMIA, or Thales.

Interagency or interstate coordination documents, including MOUs or correspondence with AAMVA or other states regarding mDL interoperability, standards development, or airport integration at including but not limited to documents regarding use at the Denver International Airport.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rebecca Williams

title: TSA Biometric Pilot Records – JFK (Expedited Request)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

created between March 1, 2025 and August 30, 2025 related to TSA biometric pilots at John F. Kennedy International Airport (JFK):

(1) Internal evaluation or pilot assessment reports prepared by TSA program offices (e.g., Requirements & Capabilities Analysis or CAT Program Office) that summarize performance, risks, or “lessons learned” from biometric deployments at JFK (Touchless ID, CAT-2, or eGates).

(2) Agreements with private vendors (such as CLEAR, IDEMIA, or similar) governing biometric deployments at JFK during this timeframe, including MOUs, pilot participation agreements, or Other Transaction Agreements (OTAs).

I request expedited processing under 5 U.S.C. § 552(a)(6)(E) and 6 C.F.R. § 5.5(e), as there is an urgent need to inform the public about TSA’s expansion of biometric surveillance at one of the nation’s busiest airports. Millions of travelers are affected, and timely disclosure is essential for public oversight and debate.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rebecca Williams
